5:
Stella, we're getting a steady stream
of readings. Be prepared to start
once the numbers cross the
threshold.
9:
Threshold has been reached. I am
ready to go.
13:
All right, stand back and cover your
ears!
21:
It is as I thought... We've also run
enough tests to safely draw an
overall conclusionâ€”
23:
Recycling elemental shards
undoubtedly warps the surrounding
mana for a period of time.
27: Then it's just as you predicted.
31:
No... It's worse. The probability of an
accident is the same, but the
severity is far worse than I originally
thought.
34:
They already have an offshore
power plant running and are in the
process of making more. There's no
time to waste.
37:
But... What can I hope to accomplish
alone?
42: I see. I know just what to do.
48:
The power plant needs to be shut
down at any cost.
53:
You sure sprung this on us outta
nowhere... Can you explain
EVERYTHING before we jump the gun
this time?
56:
This is an inert elemental shard.
We've discovered that it is extremely
hazardous to recycle it.
59:
If an energy surge happens... There
won't be a tomorrow for the people
living there.
61:
I need to stop my old friend from
continuing to use this technology...
There's a chance this will get ugly.
63: Still, can I count on you?
68:
Wow, that's the clearest explanation
you've given yet! In other words, you
need some backup, eh? We got ya!
72:
The Gaeans are SO not gonna be
happy with us again...
77:
I'm sorry, but... I appreciate what
you're doing. Thank you.
82:
Frank, you have to do something!
The plant won't last much longer!
84:
...Very well, I shall handle this. Gather
everyone and evacuate the
premises.
87:
Stop fussing and go! You know the
fewer casualties involved, the better!
89:
What a coincidence the Star Augurs
are nowhere to be found. Were we
all just disposable test subjects for
them?
91:
Hmph... What a fitting price to pay
for neglecting thorough safety
measures.
94:
Warping mana, and the resulting
monster frenzies... You were right all
along.
103:
What outstanding timing! My luck
must finally be turning around!
Wouldn't you agree, Frank?
105:
Bryce?! Is... Is it truly you? Why are
you here?
109:
Save the small talk for later! Today I
reclaim my dignity! One can never
be too prepared, and I'm here to
prove it!
112:
This... is a theory on stabilizing
elemental shards?
114:
Condensed down for a quick study,
so you can mobilize everyone and
start synthesizing the materials! No
time to waste!
118: Good thing we tagged along, huh?
121:
...Y'know, you're looking pretty
chipper for a guy whose worst
prediction came true.
125:
Hehehe... Yes, it came true, which
means I was RIGHT, in addition to
being able to show off my research!
129:
This is an alchemist's greatest
dream come true!
131:
Not a single person will be harmed
under my watch! Behold, the
supremacy of testing theories and
research! Hahaha!
137:
He's a pal of yours from way back
when, right? Go on. Talk to him.
141: Right... Excuse me for a moment.
145:
The crisis is averted with minimal
damage... What will happen to the
power plant now?
147:
I can't imagine the government
officials will remain idle. At best, the
plant will remain as a place for
study.
151:
Why not put your negotiating skills
to use in the Society? You still have
that going for you, despite your
faults as an alchemist.
153:
And if you manage to make it
happen... Here. Take this data. Keep
studying the technology, analyze,
and adapt.
155:
You gathered all this by yourself...
Are you certain? Depending on the
results, they might seal the tech
away in the end...
158:
Alchemy exists to provide a better
tomorrow for everyone. I can live
with any result, so long as we act
according to this creed.
162:
Besides, I have a feeling you'll find a
useful application for this research,
even if it's not in a form you
originally intended.
167: I just wanted to say... I'm sorry.
171:
To cling to hope, even when you've
sunk to your lowest...
173:
I appreciate the offer, but I'm afraid I
can't accept. While I've been gone,
I've taken on a rather passionate
student who needs looking after.
176:
Frank... Goodbye for now. I'm sure
we'll meet again someday.
